13/01/2011
MADRID, Spain -- Foreign Minister Trinidad Jimenez assured visiting Serbian counterpart Vuk Jeremic of Spain's support for Serbia's EU bid, Jeremic said on Wednesday (January 12th) after their meeting in Madrid.
He added the two countries will continue to co-operate on all issues related to peace and stability in the Western Balkans and the EU integration process.
Jeremic also said Spanish companies are interested in investing in Serbia.
Jimenez voiced support for the upcoming dialogue between Belgrade and Pristina and reiterated that Spain will not recognise Kosovo's independence.
(RTS, Tanjug, Beta - 12/01/11)
